      "message": "This is a valid concern with the current dict\u003cstring, variant\u003cstring, uint64, boolean\u003e\u003e approach, especially for CPER where the data is inherently nested and not always representable within this limited type set.\nI\u0027ve initiated a discussion here to get broader feedback:\nhttps://discord.com/channels/775381525260664832/1511793585127690340/1516262010696892416\nOne possible direction is to align with the Data property pattern used in Cper.events.yaml, i.e., represent this as a JSON string, which avoids lossy transformations and preserves full CPER structure.\nOtherwise, as mentioned, any sections that don’t fit the current dictionary model would require custom handling in both phosphor-logging and bmcweb, which could increase complexity and maintenance overhead.\nBased on  feedback from the discussion and update the approach accordingly.",
